# Algebra.Furey.MinimalLeftIdeal

The primitive idempotent and minimal left ideal in ℂ⊗𝕆.

## The idempotent omega

In Furey's construction (Baez convention), the primitive idempotent is built from
the privileged imaginary unit e_7. In our XOR convention, e_7 = e111.

The idempotent in Furey (arXiv:1806.00612) takes the form:
  omega = (1/2)(1 - i·e111)    (in complex scalar + imaginary octonion notation)

This satisfies omega * omega = omega (idempotent) and is minimal (primitive).

Note: The precise coefficient and sign depend on the normalization convention in
the paper. The definition here follows the convention that omega is a left-handed
projector. The ConventionBridge guarantees e111 = e_7 (Baez) in our basis.

## The minimal left ideal J

The minimal left ideal is:
  J = (ℂ⊗𝕆) * omega  (left multiplication by omega on all of ℂ⊗𝕆)

J is an 8-dimensional ℂ-subspace of ℂ⊗𝕆. As a left module over Cl(6)
(generated by the ladder operators), J carries a single irreducible
representation corresponding to one generation of SM fermions.

## Basis of J

A ℂ-basis of J consists of:
  nu     = alpha_1 * alpha_2 * alpha_3 * omega   (anti-neutrino state)
  e1_    = alpha_1† * nu                          (anti-up-quark, colour 1)
  e2_    = alpha_2† * nu                          (anti-up-quark, colour 2)
  e3_    = alpha_3† * nu                          (anti-up-quark, colour 3)
  e12    = alpha_1† * alpha_2† * nu               (electron)
  e13    = alpha_1† * alpha_3† * nu               (down-quark, colour 1)
  e23    = alpha_2† * alpha_3† * nu               (down-quark, colour 2)
  e123   = alpha_1† * alpha_2† * alpha_3† * nu    (down-quark, colour 3)

(Notation adapted from Furey; see the paper for the precise identification with
particle quantum numbers.)

## Sources

Source: Furey, arXiv:1806.00612, Section 2.
Provenance: clean-room formalization.

## Prerequisites

- `PhysicsSM.Algebra.Octonion.ComplexOctonion`
- `PhysicsSM.Algebra.Furey.LadderOperators`

## Status

